description:
&lt;p&gt;There is an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic nurse to join the team on ward 12 North Tyneside General Hospital. The successful candidate must have good verbal and written communication skills and have an interest in Elderly Care Medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a 26 bedded Elderly Care ward and support patients from the North Tyneside area with on-going rehabilitation following an acute illness associated with the older person. We also care for those patients who may have some mental health needs i.e delirium / dementia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a strong working relationship with all members of the multi disciplinary team within the hospital environment and as part of our discharge planning process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Essential Criteria&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1st Level live NMC registered Nurse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered Mentor. Mentorship qualification or relevant qualification (essential requirement for post, expectation this will be completed within an 18 month period)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thorough understanding of contemporary nursing issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring the delivery of ‘Compassion in Practice’- Nursing, Midwifery and Care Staff Vision and Strategy incorporating the 6C’s&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The successful post holder must be able to role model compassionate and inclusive leadership in order to shape the creation of a collective leadership culture within the Trust. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Closing Date: 16th November 2020&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sian Usher, Ward Manager, sian.usher@nhct.nhs.uk, 0344 811 8111 ext. 34123&lt;/p&gt;
